data.name: label1.Text
data.value: The Customer Notification Wizard will walk you through the steps required to produce printed materials for the notification of a planned Outage to customer.It will also allow you to print a list of all customers specified for reference

data.name: label31.Text
data.value: Now you need to select the types of output you would like to generate from customer records you have specified. You can select any number of output options and the application will work you through the setup of each. You will also be able to preview any reports before they are actually printed.

data.name: label22.Text
data.value: Here you need to specify the outage date and duration. The dates must be future Dates and time ON must be after time OFF. If the power will be out of two time spans, Click on "Add Additional ...." check box and define the second outage date and times.

data.name: label13.Text
data.value: The list of customers you have identified on the previous pages will be sent to the Planned Shutdown Coordinator (PSC).Once the customer notification request is vetted and approved, shutdown notification letters will be sent. Please note that clicking the send button below will begint he process that may send outage notification letters to customer. If you send a request and need to modify or cancel it, you need to contact PSC. After clicking "Send" you will get a message indicating that the data has been sent successfully and will be given request number so you can refer this job if you need to make any changes. You can also request a copy of the email that is sent to the PSC.

data.name: label27.Text
data.value: To print on the back of letters / postcards, you must print or copy all the letters / postcards then put them back into the printer so that the addresses can be printed on the reverse side of the paper.

data.name: label32.Text
data.value: Now you need to select the types of output you would like to generate from customer records you have specified. You can select any number of output options and the application will work you through the setup of each. You will also be able to preview any reports before they are actually printed.
